1
00:01:40,670 --> 00:01:45,920
[Speed and Love]

2
00:01:46,330 --> 00:01:48,770
[Episode 4]

3
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,990
[Speeding Auto House]

4
00:01:53,550 --> 00:01:55,680
[Episode 4]

5
00:02:48,410 --> 00:02:49,340
It's about time.

6
00:02:49,350 --> 00:02:50,750
We can't wait any longer.

7
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:18,050
Sister.

8
00:03:19,430 --> 00:03:20,430
What's wrong?

9
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:24,990
Why are you crying?

10
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:27,990
Do you know where Jin Zhao is?

11
00:03:57,870 --> 00:03:58,660
Thank you.

12
00:05:44,909 --> 00:05:46,110
Why didn't you leave?

13
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:49,590
Because I forgot to tell you something.

14
00:06:02,910 --> 00:06:04,030
Happy birthday,

15
00:06:04,740 --> 00:06:05,660
Zhao.

16
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:30,780
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

17
00:06:30,950 --> 00:06:34,100
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

18
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:37,280
Come on,
let's blow out the candles together.

19
00:06:41,659 --> 00:06:43,860
Zhao, when is your birthday?

20
00:06:51,909 --> 00:06:53,150
Then just let Jin Zhao and Jin Mu

21
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:55,150
share the same birthday from now on.

22
00:06:55,409 --> 00:06:57,610
Mu's birthday will be Zhao's birthday.

23
00:06:57,740 --> 00:07:00,200
Together from dawn till dusk,
never to part.

24
00:07:32,540 --> 00:07:34,000
Happy birthday to you too.

25
00:07:37,060 --> 00:07:37,820
Mu.

26
00:07:53,930 --> 00:07:55,930
You haven't eaten all day, have you?

27
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:03,050
Wait for me.

28
00:08:04,340 --> 00:08:05,710
I'll take you out to eat.

29
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:28,880
You cried again?

30
00:08:30,780 --> 00:08:31,860
How did you know?

31
00:08:33,940 --> 00:08:35,940
Your eyes are swollen like walnuts.

32
00:08:38,230 --> 00:08:40,690
The more you rub them,
the worse they'll get.

33
00:08:41,539 --> 00:08:42,940
It's all your fault.

34
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:45,940
Why blame me?

35
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:48,430
I'm not telling you.

36
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:51,150
If you don't tell me,

37
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:53,210
how can I know if it's really my fault?

38
00:08:55,150 --> 00:08:56,480
Who told you I was there?

39
00:08:58,780 --> 00:08:59,700
Jin Xin.

40
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,560
That kid is better than Jin Qiang.

41
00:09:09,540 --> 00:09:10,660
Are you doing well

42
00:09:12,310 --> 00:09:13,310
here?

43
00:09:15,150 --> 00:09:16,110
What do you mean

44
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:18,110
by "well"?

45
00:09:18,990 --> 00:09:19,870
I mean,

46
00:09:20,910 --> 00:09:21,990
are you adjusting?

47
00:09:23,270 --> 00:09:24,630
After Jin Xin was born,

48
00:09:25,630 --> 00:09:27,540
do you feel like you don't belong?

49
00:09:30,660 --> 00:09:31,350
It's fine.

50
00:09:33,410 --> 00:09:34,870
What do you mean by "fine"?

51
00:09:38,060 --> 00:09:38,870
I'm used to it.

52
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:49,700
Let's go.

53
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,160
I'll take you somewhere.

54
00:10:03,910 --> 00:10:05,030
Do you have any cake left?

55
00:10:05,030 --> 00:10:05,660
Yes, we do.

56
00:10:06,150 --> 00:10:07,110
Please come in.

57
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:16,060
At this hour,

58
00:10:16,060 --> 00:10:17,660
all the pastry chefs have gone home.

59
00:10:17,660 --> 00:10:18,750
See if there's anything you like.

60
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:20,580
If not, we can try somewhere else.

61
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:22,780
I'll take this strawberry cake then.

62
00:10:26,390 --> 00:10:28,580
Could you please box up
this strawberry cake for me?

63
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:29,420
Just a moment.

64
00:10:32,420 --> 00:10:34,220
Is there anything else you want?

65
00:10:35,230 --> 00:10:36,510
Can I have a drink?

66
00:10:38,540 --> 00:10:39,180
Sure.

67
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,680
Birthday girl gets what she wants.

68
00:11:15,780 --> 00:11:16,780
Make a wish now.

69
00:11:23,940 --> 00:11:24,870
You make one too.

70
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:31,870
When is your actual birthday?

71
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:36,520
It doesn't matter.

72
00:11:37,990 --> 00:11:39,350
How can it not matter?

73
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:40,820
That was the first day

74
00:11:40,820 --> 00:11:42,990
you truly came into this world.

75
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:47,640
I've gone over 20 years
without caring about it.

76
00:11:48,110 --> 00:11:49,110
I only know

77
00:11:49,850 --> 00:11:51,650
the day you came into this world.

78
00:11:59,850 --> 00:12:00,650
What's wrong?

79
00:12:02,460 --> 00:12:04,050
You're not going to cry, are you?

80
00:12:04,050 --> 00:12:04,930
No.

81
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:08,540
I just suddenly feel

82
00:12:08,820 --> 00:12:10,110
so sorry for you.

83
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:15,350
♪ Perhaps the weather's damp and mild ♪

84
00:12:15,350 --> 00:12:16,300
It's okay.

85
00:12:16,670 --> 00:12:20,500
♪ Perhaps it's about the habit
of bearing ♪

86
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:21,220
The candle is about to go out.

87
00:12:21,220 --> 00:12:23,630
♪ A certain bitter emotion ♪

88
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:24,490
Make a wish now.

89
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:30,590
♪ For you, it's all too easy ♪

90
00:12:31,540 --> 00:12:31,630
♪ To be happy or heartbroken,
as transparent as I can be ♪

91
00:12:31,630 --> 00:12:32,580
The first wish

92
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:34,580
needs to be said aloud to come true.

93
00:12:34,580 --> 00:12:35,870
I wish we

94
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:37,210
could soon find out

95
00:12:37,270 --> 00:12:38,250
when your actual birthday is.

96
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:44,150
♪ Crossing the line for love,
I've walked 1,000 km ♪

97
00:12:45,490 --> 00:12:51,650
♪ Brave enough to be sure is my instinct ♪

98
00:12:51,810 --> 00:12:52,960
♪ I believe ♪

99
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:56,580
♪ Maybe it just takes a little resolve ♪

100
00:12:56,580 --> 00:12:57,410
As for the second wish,

101
00:12:57,410 --> 00:12:58,060
♪ To turn wishes into shooting stars ♪

102
00:12:58,060 --> 00:12:59,420
I won't say it out loud,

103
00:12:59,700 --> 00:13:01,220
or it won't come true.

104
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:03,580
♪ Mirroring the eyes that gaze at me ♪

105
00:13:03,580 --> 00:13:04,700
For my second wish,

106
00:13:05,230 --> 00:13:08,020
may every year bring us such joy,

107
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:09,870
and every moment such bliss,

108
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:12,460
together from dawn till dusk,
never to part.

109
00:13:20,030 --> 00:13:22,930
♪ The crash of waves comes and goes ♪

110
00:13:22,930 --> 00:13:23,760
Eat the cake.

111
00:13:26,870 --> 00:13:30,350
♪ After leaning on you and hesitation ♪

112
00:13:30,460 --> 00:13:30,570
Thank you.

113
00:13:30,570 --> 00:13:33,230
♪ I've never been so steadfast and true ♪

114
00:13:33,230 --> 00:13:34,010
You eat too.

115
00:13:34,010 --> 00:13:35,180
♪ My love needs to stay clear-eyed ♪

116
00:13:35,180 --> 00:13:36,180
I'm not used to it.

117
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:37,730
It's too sweet.

118
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:44,390
♪ After the scorching ache,
I still reach for a sincere heart ♪

119
00:13:44,390 --> 00:13:45,540
Just to let you know in advance,

120
00:13:45,540 --> 00:13:47,140
I don't handle alcohol well.

121
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:48,200
I might act crazy if I drink too much.

122
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:53,060
♪ Crossing the line for love,
I've walked 1,000 km ♪

123
00:13:53,060 --> 00:13:54,110
Then should I

124
00:13:55,460 --> 00:13:56,230
♪ Brave enough to be sure is my instinct ♪

125
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:57,560
open this bottle or not?

126
00:14:01,620 --> 00:14:02,460
♪ I believe
maybe it just takes a little resolve ♪

127
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:04,260
Maybe we shouldn't open it then.

128
00:14:07,010 --> 00:14:09,230
♪ To turn wishes into shooting stars ♪

129
00:14:09,230 --> 00:14:10,490
Drink it if you want to.

130
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:11,630
♪ Mirroring the eyes that gaze at me ♪

131
00:14:11,630 --> 00:14:12,830
I'll be there for you.

132
00:14:15,370 --> 00:14:16,870
♪ Fearless as a moth
darting into the fire ♪

133
00:14:16,870 --> 00:14:17,580
Come on.

134
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:19,350
Happy birthday.

135
00:14:20,490 --> 00:14:28,550
♪ I'd rewrite the ending
of missed chances 1,000 times ♪

136
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:35,190
♪ Crossing the line for love,
I've walked 1,000 km ♪

137
00:14:35,780 --> 00:14:36,630
I'm so happy.

138
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:37,030
♪ Brave enough to be sure is my instinct ♪

139
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:38,150
After all these years,

140
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:41,280
I never thought
I'd celebrate a birthday with you again.

141
00:14:42,710 --> 00:14:43,910
♪ I believe ♪

142
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:46,350
♪ Maybe it just takes a little resolve ♪

143
00:14:46,350 --> 00:14:47,980
That Chris is so old.

144
00:14:47,980 --> 00:14:49,300
♪ To turn wishes into shooting stars ♪

145
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,430
Besides being rich,

146
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:52,090
he has absolutely no other good qualities.

147
00:14:52,090 --> 00:14:53,270
♪ Mirroring the eyes that gaze at me ♪

148
00:14:53,270 --> 00:14:55,580
Mom still wants to go back
to Canada with him.

149
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:58,390
I'm really worried Mom is being deceived.

150
00:14:58,870 --> 00:15:01,070
Your mother isn't someone who settles.

151
00:15:01,310 --> 00:15:02,880
She didn't find anyone else
after splitting with Jin Qiang.

152
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:04,340
♪ Crossing the orbit,
stepping into your life ♪

153
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:06,200
This time, she must truly like him

154
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:08,630
to agree to marry again.

155
00:15:09,150 --> 00:15:10,880
You should trust her judgment.

156
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:18,870
You call Dad "Jin Qiang"

157
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:20,230
instead of "Dad."

158
00:15:20,820 --> 00:15:24,870
You refer to Jiang Yinghan
as "your mother" rather than "Mom."

159
00:15:26,540 --> 00:15:28,600
You've known all along, haven't you?

160
00:15:31,050 --> 00:15:32,850
When I went to Jin Qiang's house,

161
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:37,330
you weren't even born yet.

162
00:15:50,180 --> 00:15:52,240
What about you? When did you find out?

163
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:54,520
I've known for a long time.

164
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:05,980
What did you think after finding out?

165
00:16:28,770 --> 00:16:31,220
Mom sold the old house in Nanjing.

166
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:32,540
I might really

167
00:16:32,540 --> 00:16:34,750
have nowhere to go anymore.

168
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:40,040
I won't really become homeless, will I?

169
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:45,150
What are you laughing at?

170
00:16:58,180 --> 00:17:00,780
I suddenly feel so pitiful.

171
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:04,109
Dad doesn't care about me,
Mom doesn't want me,

172
00:17:04,109 --> 00:17:05,710
and Brother doesn't love me.

173
00:17:10,849 --> 00:17:12,250
Brother doesn't love me.

174
00:17:20,180 --> 00:17:21,510
What do you want me to do?

175
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,050
Let's go.

176
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:43,970
Time to go home.

177
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:46,320
No, I don't want to go back yet.

178
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:51,280
That habit of staying out all night
isn't good.

179
00:17:53,630 --> 00:17:55,700
I am not with a bad person.

180
00:17:58,160 --> 00:18:00,090
How do you know I'm not a bad person?

181
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:03,390
Well, you haven't done anything bad to me.

182
00:18:09,390 --> 00:18:10,990
Did you bring your house key?

183
00:18:12,220 --> 00:18:13,350
What a coincidence.

184
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,080
I didn't bring it.

185
00:18:19,390 --> 00:18:20,520
What a coincidence.

186
00:18:22,220 --> 00:18:23,330
I have a spare one.

187
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:32,090
It's raining heavily outside.

188
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:35,710
It would be troublesome
to go out in this weather.

189
00:18:35,940 --> 00:18:36,910
I have a car.

190
00:18:39,830 --> 00:18:42,070
Can't we wait until the rain stops?

191
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:43,220
Bargaining?

192
00:18:44,740 --> 00:18:46,200
I've had too much to drink.

193
00:18:47,390 --> 00:18:48,990
Let's go. It's getting late.

194
00:18:51,850 --> 00:18:54,490
Does your offer still stand?

195
00:18:55,110 --> 00:18:55,910
What offer?

196
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,640
Letting me stay here.

197
00:19:14,890 --> 00:19:16,130
I'm not your brother.

198
00:19:17,980 --> 00:19:19,840
Do you think this is appropriate?

199
00:19:20,870 --> 00:19:21,940
Yes, it's fine.

200
00:19:22,470 --> 00:19:24,260
The water heater at Dad's place is broken.

201
00:19:24,260 --> 00:19:25,920
I can't even take a hot shower.

202
00:19:26,150 --> 00:19:28,700
You know how hot it is here.

203
00:19:28,790 --> 00:19:30,390
If I can't shower before bed,

204
00:19:30,390 --> 00:19:31,980
it'll be very uncomfortable.

205
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:33,180
I'm new here.

206
00:19:33,180 --> 00:19:35,870
I can't handle cold water showers.

207
00:19:45,290 --> 00:19:46,150
Just one night.

208
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:12,940
Oh no.

209
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,370
Why am I so unlucky?

210
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:16,640
Having my period at a time like this.

211
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:28,260
I've left some clothes here for you.

212
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:35,680
What's wrong?

213
00:20:39,370 --> 00:20:40,700
Does your stomach hurt?

214
00:20:45,070 --> 00:20:47,070
Is your stomach upset from the beer?

215
00:21:00,350 --> 00:21:01,310
Are you...

216
00:21:01,330 --> 00:21:02,290
Yes.

217
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:04,420
That's right.

218
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:05,520
That's right.

219
00:21:06,010 --> 00:21:08,320
But it seems we can't order takeout here.

220
00:21:10,660 --> 00:21:11,590
You take a shower first.

221
00:21:11,590 --> 00:21:12,520
I'll go buy some.

222
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:18,420
What are you buying today, handsome?

223
00:21:18,630 --> 00:21:20,830
Please support my business more often.

224
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:24,940
Do you need any help?

225
00:21:26,530 --> 00:21:28,730
Just let me know if you need assistance.

226
00:21:28,790 --> 00:21:30,190
Did you get the right one?

227
00:21:37,870 --> 00:21:39,980
Would you like
to join our 10-baht promotion?

228
00:21:39,980 --> 00:21:44,460
Just add 10 more baht.

229
00:21:45,040 --> 00:21:48,910
You can choose anything from this shelf.

230
00:21:49,650 --> 00:21:50,580
It's a good deal.

231
00:21:59,250 --> 00:22:00,910
I bought everything you need.

232
00:22:01,390 --> 00:22:02,450
I'll wait outside.

233
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:04,100
Call me if you need anything.

234
00:22:23,930 --> 00:22:25,610
I'm done. You can shower now.

235
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:46,050
I'll give you these slippers
after I get into bed.

236
00:22:59,530 --> 00:23:00,730
Where will you sleep?

237
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:01,520
Next door.

238
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,060
At Sanlai's place.

239
00:23:09,940 --> 00:23:10,800
Get some sleep.

240
00:23:42,020 --> 00:23:42,820
What's wrong?

241
00:23:43,940 --> 00:23:45,020
My stomach hurts.

242
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:47,610
I'll take you to the hospital.

243
00:23:47,610 --> 00:23:48,450
No need.

244
00:23:50,110 --> 00:23:52,630
It's my period. It'll get better soon.

245
00:24:00,090 --> 00:24:01,090
Does it hurt a lot?

246
00:24:10,770 --> 00:24:11,570
Wait a moment.

247
00:24:13,420 --> 00:24:14,390
It says here

248
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:17,050
you should warm it with your hands.

249
00:24:22,330 --> 00:24:23,530
Then press

250
00:24:24,020 --> 00:24:25,350
the Guanyuan acupoint.

251
00:24:25,550 --> 00:24:27,150
Where is the Guanyuan acupoint?

252
00:24:27,150 --> 00:24:28,010
It's about 10 cm

253
00:24:28,180 --> 00:24:29,830
right below your navel.

254
00:24:32,020 --> 00:24:33,180
It's not working.

255
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:34,460
Press with your finger.

256
00:24:34,460 --> 00:24:35,790
I am pressing it.

257
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:38,470
It's here.

258
00:24:46,980 --> 00:24:49,740
Your hands are so warm. Warm me up.

259
00:25:01,365 --> 00:25:07,365
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

260
00:25:03,390 --> 00:25:04,500
Feeling better?

261
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:11,770
Don't move.

262
00:26:01,940 --> 00:26:03,590
Why did you bring him back?

263
00:26:04,180 --> 00:26:06,070
Don't you know our situation?

264
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:07,740
I'm pregnant.

265
00:26:08,350 --> 00:26:09,460
How can I manage?

266
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:10,980
Can you afford to raise him?

267
00:26:10,980 --> 00:26:13,460
One more child just means
one more set of dishes.

268
00:26:13,460 --> 00:26:14,840
You're making a fuss over nothing.

269
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:15,910
Easy for you to say.

270
00:26:15,930 --> 00:26:17,430
Is it just about an extra set of dishes?

271
00:26:17,430 --> 00:26:18,500
Can you really support him?

272
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:19,830
Charles was my brother.

273
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:21,110
He had an accident at the racetrack.

274
00:26:21,110 --> 00:26:22,570
I can't abandon his child!

275
00:26:22,630 --> 00:26:23,940
His father was just a daredevil!

276
00:26:23,940 --> 00:26:25,180
I'm a daredevil too!

277
00:26:25,590 --> 00:26:26,150
You...

278
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:30,150
Jin Qiang, let me tell you.

279
00:26:30,660 --> 00:26:31,920
I don't agree with this.

280
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:33,120
Do whatever you want.

281
00:26:37,430 --> 00:26:39,690
You just gave birth
and don't even take care of your baby.

282
00:26:39,690 --> 00:26:41,550
You always run off to dance class.

283
00:26:41,780 --> 00:26:43,020
What else can I do?

284
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:44,840
We still need to live our lives.

285
00:26:44,910 --> 00:26:46,770
I need to earn money for my family.

286
00:26:48,430 --> 00:26:49,180
I'm done talking to you.

287
00:26:49,180 --> 00:26:50,910
The baby's awake. I need to breastfeed.

288
00:26:50,910 --> 00:26:51,550
That's it.

289
00:26:55,260 --> 00:26:56,020
Sweetheart.

290
00:27:10,020 --> 00:27:11,820
My daughter is almost 2 years old

291
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:13,870
and still can't talk.

292
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:15,870
I'm really worried.

293
00:27:16,730 --> 00:27:17,730
I don't know

294
00:27:17,770 --> 00:27:19,900
if it has something to do with Jin Zhao.

295
00:27:20,490 --> 00:27:21,380
I just feel like

296
00:27:21,410 --> 00:27:23,250
my life isn't going well.

297
00:27:23,270 --> 00:27:24,400
You know what I mean?

298
00:27:28,740 --> 00:27:29,410
Anyway...

299
00:27:31,050 --> 00:27:32,310
I've already decided.

300
00:27:37,530 --> 00:27:39,190
Thank you for your help, Miss.

301
00:27:40,310 --> 00:27:41,070
Jin Zhao,

302
00:27:41,590 --> 00:27:43,910
you must listen to your teacher there

303
00:27:44,030 --> 00:27:46,130
and get along with the other children.

304
00:27:46,130 --> 00:27:48,460
I'll come visit you when I can, okay?

305
00:27:50,860 --> 00:27:52,720
Miss, I'll leave him in your care.

306
00:27:53,260 --> 00:27:53,910
Come.

307
00:27:55,550 --> 00:27:56,870
Brother.

308
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,430
Brother.

309
00:28:10,110 --> 00:28:12,290
[Speeding Auto House]

310
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:16,070
Master,

311
00:28:16,220 --> 00:28:17,780
why are you starting work so early today?

312
00:28:17,780 --> 00:28:20,240
Want some coconut juice?
It's really fresh.

313
00:28:20,910 --> 00:28:21,700
Keep it down.

314
00:28:23,070 --> 00:28:24,000
I don't want any.

315
00:28:24,110 --> 00:28:25,090
Then I'll take it inside.

316
00:28:25,090 --> 00:28:25,750
Don't go in.

317
00:28:28,740 --> 00:28:29,740
Who's in there?

318
00:28:30,870 --> 00:28:31,910
A heavy sleeper.

319
00:28:34,220 --> 00:28:35,420
A heavy sleeper?

320
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:38,910
Brandy, Yang.

321
00:28:39,590 --> 00:28:40,310
Breakfast is ready.

322
00:28:40,310 --> 00:28:41,520
I bought it from miles away.

323
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:42,590
Be quiet.

324
00:28:42,980 --> 00:28:43,780
What's wrong?

325
00:28:43,870 --> 00:28:44,940
There's someone in Master's room.

326
00:28:44,940 --> 00:28:45,940
Someone's there?

327
00:28:46,780 --> 00:28:47,500
Who is it?

328
00:28:48,590 --> 00:28:49,660
I don't know.

329
00:28:50,190 --> 00:28:52,070
Seems someone has stayed in the lounge
since last night.

330
00:28:52,070 --> 00:28:53,660
Doesn't he forbid others
from staying in his room?

331
00:28:53,660 --> 00:28:55,310
Yes, who could it be?

332
00:28:57,620 --> 00:28:58,580
Snakey?

333
00:28:59,260 --> 00:29:00,020
No way.

334
00:29:00,220 --> 00:29:01,550
Last time she came to the shop,

335
00:29:01,550 --> 00:29:02,730
she insisted on going to the lounge

336
00:29:02,730 --> 00:29:04,860
and casually lay down on Brandy's bed.

337
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:06,350
When he came back,

338
00:29:06,550 --> 00:29:07,450
upon seeing that,

339
00:29:07,450 --> 00:29:09,680
he grabbed her by the collar
and threw her out.

340
00:29:09,680 --> 00:29:10,770
Snakey was so angry

341
00:29:11,040 --> 00:29:13,040
she hasn't been back for a long time.

342
00:29:13,220 --> 00:29:14,380
It can't be Snakey.

343
00:29:14,500 --> 00:29:15,410
Right.

344
00:29:17,310 --> 00:29:18,630
Then who could it be

345
00:29:18,980 --> 00:29:20,380
that he's so tolerant of?

346
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:41,570
Did it start?

347
00:29:42,450 --> 00:29:43,700
Why is there no response?

348
00:29:43,700 --> 00:29:44,660
No, it didn't.

349
00:29:45,610 --> 00:29:47,570
What's the problem then?

350
00:29:48,190 --> 00:29:51,590
The spark plugs have been replaced.
What about the fuel line?

351
00:29:51,890 --> 00:29:53,820
It's not about the fuel line at all.

352
00:29:55,100 --> 00:29:55,900
The throttle?

353
00:29:56,070 --> 00:29:57,180
The throttle is fine.

354
00:29:57,180 --> 00:29:58,150
I've checked it.

355
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:00,770
Then why won't it start?

356
00:30:01,140 --> 00:30:02,800
Have you checked the battery?

357
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:04,450
Look.

358
00:30:06,570 --> 00:30:07,970
Could it be the fuel pump?

359
00:30:22,750 --> 00:30:24,190
I don't think so.

360
00:30:41,830 --> 00:30:43,030
-Who is it?
-Who is it?

361
00:30:44,500 --> 00:30:45,870
W-Who are you?

362
00:30:47,330 --> 00:30:48,990
Hello, I'm Jiang Mu,

363
00:30:49,020 --> 00:30:50,480
Jin Zhao's little sister.

364
00:31:03,350 --> 00:31:04,180
Your car has

365
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:06,010
a loose intake pressure sensor.

366
00:31:10,700 --> 00:31:12,030
What are you looking at?

367
00:31:12,350 --> 00:31:13,280
Get back to work.

368
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:27,120
Why aren't you wearing pants?

369
00:31:27,120 --> 00:31:28,090
I am.

370
00:31:30,570 --> 00:31:32,300
Is your stomach still hurting?

371
00:31:37,700 --> 00:31:39,120
Go change into long pants.

372
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:40,850
And come out for breakfast. Go.

373
00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:53,120
I don't eat carrots.

374
00:31:55,970 --> 00:31:57,300
No green onions either.

375
00:32:02,500 --> 00:32:03,160
Move aside.

376
00:32:10,980 --> 00:32:12,180
What are you laughing at?

377
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:14,110
I'm not afraid of the hot oil.

378
00:32:14,220 --> 00:32:15,110
I just...

379
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:17,440
It just happened too suddenly.

380
00:32:18,700 --> 00:32:19,700
Can you cook?

381
00:32:20,630 --> 00:32:21,550
Of course I can.

382
00:32:22,630 --> 00:32:24,260
Don't underestimate me.

383
00:32:24,870 --> 00:32:26,660
I'm a quick learner.

384
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:27,700
It's just that before,

385
00:32:27,700 --> 00:32:29,900
I didn't have many chances to practice.

386
00:32:37,580 --> 00:32:40,170
You can cook and make dumplings.

387
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,630
Looks like you're quite good
in the kitchen.

388
00:32:42,630 --> 00:32:44,230
Don't think too highly of me.

389
00:32:46,500 --> 00:32:48,900
I just had more opportunities to practice.

390
00:33:04,150 --> 00:33:05,240
Do you have time later?

391
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:07,760
Could you help me unpack my suitcase?

392
00:33:07,980 --> 00:33:09,510
All my clothes are in there.

393
00:33:13,660 --> 00:33:14,460
Is that okay?

394
00:33:15,550 --> 00:33:17,280
Did I agree to let you stay here?

395
00:33:18,830 --> 00:33:20,630
Didn't you say so last night?

396
00:33:22,110 --> 00:33:23,310
I said just one night.

397
00:33:23,550 --> 00:33:24,860
You've already slept here for one night.

398
00:33:24,860 --> 00:33:26,390
I haven't had enough sleep.

399
00:33:31,590 --> 00:33:32,840
That's insane.

400
00:33:33,530 --> 00:33:35,440
I'm starting to doubt my ears.

401
00:33:36,020 --> 00:33:37,070
I never thought

402
00:33:37,260 --> 00:33:38,660
Master would finally...

403
00:33:40,350 --> 00:33:42,180
Find love at last.

404
00:33:45,530 --> 00:33:47,290
Can I stay a few more nights?

405
00:33:55,990 --> 00:33:56,750
No way.

406
00:34:02,450 --> 00:34:04,780
How about 2 nights? Not counting tonight.

407
00:34:15,540 --> 00:34:16,940
Finish your vegetables.

408
00:34:17,230 --> 00:34:18,760
Don't pick out the carrots.

409
00:34:18,940 --> 00:34:20,870
You're so stubborn.

410
00:34:21,020 --> 00:34:22,280
You're not my brother.

411
00:34:22,679 --> 00:34:24,080
You're too controlling.

412
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:17,550
Lin Sui,

413
00:35:18,130 --> 00:35:18,980
we've checked all surveillance footage

414
00:35:18,980 --> 00:35:20,110
from that night on the mountain,

415
00:35:20,110 --> 00:35:22,440
but couldn't find any clear facial shots.

416
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:43,140
The other cars have been left far behind.

417
00:36:04,950 --> 00:36:05,880
The 11th turn.

418
00:36:06,310 --> 00:36:07,640
Whose black car is that?

419
00:36:07,700 --> 00:36:08,620
I'm sorry, Lin Sui.

420
00:36:08,620 --> 00:36:09,620
It's not one of ours.

421
00:36:09,620 --> 00:36:10,890
The road probably
hasn't been properly blocked off.

422
00:36:10,890 --> 00:36:12,490
It's just a passing vehicle.

423
00:37:06,250 --> 00:37:08,480
♪ Make it fast, never slow down ♪

424
00:37:08,500 --> 00:37:10,980
♪ Show off my extraordinary form ♪

425
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:12,120
♪ Speeding love ♪

426
00:37:12,140 --> 00:37:13,540
♪ Whether I succeed or fail ♪

427
00:37:13,560 --> 00:37:15,710
♪ I just want to be free ♪

428
00:37:15,740 --> 00:37:18,560
♪ Make my name be known
throughout the world ♪

429
00:37:18,580 --> 00:37:20,660
♪ You just wait and see ♪

430
00:37:21,060 --> 00:37:24,060
That car's got over 1,000 HP
and 2,000 lb-ft of torque.

431
00:37:25,140 --> 00:37:28,140
By the sound, it's not an ordinary rotor.

432
00:37:28,350 --> 00:37:30,270
A two-rotor, three-rotor,

433
00:37:30,580 --> 00:37:31,500
or even

434
00:37:31,910 --> 00:37:33,620
a four-rotor is possible.

435
00:37:33,980 --> 00:37:35,100
But we've checked

436
00:37:35,100 --> 00:37:35,910
the largest modified car gatherings

437
00:37:35,910 --> 00:37:37,190
in Manshi,

438
00:37:37,750 --> 00:37:39,610
but couldn't find that black car.

439
00:37:39,810 --> 00:37:41,850
Then find the person.

440
00:37:42,240 --> 00:37:43,670
In Southeast Asia, no more than 5 people

441
00:37:43,670 --> 00:37:45,190
can fabricate

442
00:37:45,210 --> 00:37:46,920
a two-rotor or more.

443
00:37:47,270 --> 00:37:48,710
Go out on the streets now.

444
00:37:48,870 --> 00:37:51,670
When you hear a rotor sound, open the hood

445
00:37:51,690 --> 00:37:52,820
and check one by one.

446
00:37:54,580 --> 00:37:55,780
What are you waiting for?

447
00:37:55,780 --> 00:37:56,540
Hurry up!

448
00:37:58,250 --> 00:37:59,050
Got it.

449
00:38:07,870 --> 00:38:10,130
Even if I have to turn Manshi upside down,

450
00:38:10,250 --> 00:38:12,040
I will find you.
